            "family": {
                "name": "Fly",
                "type": "monster_family",
                "sections": [
                    {
                        "name": "Fly Species",
                        "type": "section",
                        "text": "The giant fly presented here is but the most common of these unsettlingly oversized pests. Others can grow much larger, such as the blood-drinking glutton fly, the highly toxic and foulsmelling blight fly, and the immensely bloated plague fly\u2014a nauseating creature ironically incapable of flight that fattens itself on undead flesh and carries a host of awful diseases.",
                        "sources": [
